"description": "<p>Requisition ID:  78557 </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><u><a href=\"https://www.nexteraenergyresources.com/what-we-do/energy-marketing.html\">NextEra Energy Resources</a></u> is the world's largest generator of renewable energy from the wind and sun, and a world leader in battery storage. We provide energy-related products and services that grow our economy, protect the environment, support our communities and help customers meet their energy needs. We are leading the decarbonization of the U.S. economy with our goal to reach Real Zero carbon emissions from our operations by 2045 while improving customer affordability and reliability. Are you interested in creating a cleaner environment for future generations? Join our world-class, innovative team today.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Position Specific Description</p>\n<p><p>The ideal Marketing Specialist is very versatile and can support the marketing department in a variety of areas. This individual will provide the necessary support to initiate, develop, implement, and/or measure projects, programs, and initiatives. The ideal candidate has excellent written and verbal communication skills, as well as being very detailed-oriented and well-organized. This role will lead the planning and execution of event details including travel, booth setup and teardown, and the ordering and shipping of swag and printed materials for conferences and trade shows.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develops and manages a comprehensive events calendar including all components of planning and execution for conferences and trade shows</li>\n<li>Partners with business stakeholders to define marketing objectives and advertising initiatives</li>\n<li>Assists in tracking the team’s progress against the marketing operational plan</li>\n<li>Writes and edits copy – for both internal and external audiences – including, but not limited to: articles, scripts, marketing collateral, web content, forum responses, blogs, newsletters, social media posts, press releases, sales collateral, email campaigns, training, and conference materials</li>\n<li>Maintains library of marketing assets on shared drive</li>\n<li>Develops and executes a content calendar to ensure consistent social media activity (posts) that aligns with brand persona to engage target audiences</li>\n<li>Coordinates with Customer Care and Quality Assurance for handling of online reputational management issues</li>\n<li>Manages external relationships with vendors (graphic designers, printers, etc.) to ensure on-time, on-budget delivery of high-quality communications materials</li>\n<li>Stays up-to-date on the latest marketing trends, tools, technologies, and platforms as well as industry-specific news</li>\n<li>Knowledge shares with colleagues to establish a team culture of collaboration, innovation, curiosity, and passion</li>\n<li>Demonstrates discipline and organization in executing projects, while building and maintaining great relationships with co-workers, stakeholders, and agency partners</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Additional Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with Hubpot email campaigns</li>\n<li>Experience with social media management tools</li>\n<li>Energy industry experience a plus</li>\n<li>Ability to travel occasionally for events and conferences</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of Adobe Creative Suite (InDesign, Photoshop, etc.) a plus</li>\n<li>Ability to accurately and consistently follow brand guidelines, AP style, and company communication standards</li>\n</ul></p>\n<h2>Job Overview</h2>\n<p>This job is responsible for assisting with projects from the earliest stages of concept and development through to successful, on-time completion as measured by achievement of metrics. Employees in this role provide support in developing and executing marketing plans and initiatives to support business objectives. Individuals in this position are expected to understand needs and help to develop marketing solutions.</p><h2>Job Duties &amp; Responsibilities</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Assists with marketing planning</li>\n<li>Develops key campaign tactics using research and analytics to drive planning and messaging</li>\n<li>Follows established processes, demonstrating discipline and organization in executing assignments and plans</li>\n<li>Builds and maintains great relationships with co-workers</li>\n<li>Tracks performance and progress using quantifiable metrics</li>\n<li>Communicates frequently with cross-functional groups</li>\n<li>Works at both business unit and corporate levels</li>\n<li>Performs other job-related duties as assigned</li>\n</ul><h2>Required Qualifications</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor's Degree</li>\n<li>Experience: 2+ years</li>\n</ul><h2>Preferred Qualifications</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>None</li>\n</ul><p> </p>\n<p>Employee Group:  Exempt<br/>\nEmployee Type:  Full Time<br/>\nJob Category:  Marketing/Communications<br/>\nOrganization:  NextEra Energy Project Management, LLC <br/>\nRelocation Provided:  No</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>NextEra Energy is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to race, color, age, national origin, religion, marital status, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, genetics, disability, protected veteran status or any other basis prohibited by law. We are committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>NextEra Energy provides reasonable accommodation in its application and selection process for qualified individuals, including accommodations related to compliance with conditional job offer requirements, consistent with federal, state, and local laws. Supporting medical or religious documentation will be required where applicable and permitted by applicable law. To request a reasonable accommodation, please send an e-mail to <a href=\"mailto:recruiting-coordinator.sharedmailbox@nexteraenergy.com\">recruiting-coordinator.sharedmailbox@nexteraenergy.com</a>, providing your name, telephone number and the best time for us to reach you. Alternatively, you may call 1-844-694-4748. Please do not use this line to inquire about your application status.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>NextEra Energy will not discharge or in any other manner discriminate against employees or applicants because they have inquired about, discussed, or disclosed their own pay or the pay of another employee or applicant. However, employees who have access to the compensation information of other employees or applicants as a part of their essential job functions cannot disclose the pay of other employees or applicants to individuals who do not otherwise have access to compensation information, unless the disclosure is (a) in response to a formal complaint or charge, (b) in furtherance of an investigation, proceeding, hearing, or action, including an investigation conducted by the employer, or (c) consistent with the contractor’s legal duty to furnish information.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>NextEra Energy does not accept any unsolicited resumes or referrals from any third-party recruiting firms or agencies. Please see our <a href=\"https://jobs.nexteraenergy.com/content/Third-Party-Recruiters/?locale=en_US&amp;previewLink=true&amp;referrerSave=false&amp;token=a4un1TiWoTYJimvq3RG1Jw%3D%3D\" target=\"_blank\">policy</a> for more information.</p>\n<p> </p>",
