"description": "Top Hat's dynamic courseware empowers educators and students by delivering personalized, meaningful and equitable learning in every course. Providing educators with interactive course content, tools, assessment capabilities, and insights in a single, easy-to-use application.<br/>Millions of students at 750 leading North American colleges and universities use Top Hat to teach and engage with students before, during, and after class, in both in-person and online education. Are you ready to help us change the future of higher ed and deliver equitable education for millions of students?<br/>Top Hat is looking for a Lifecycle Marketing Specialist to create and launch educator and student marketing programs to nurture, acquire and retain existing and prospective customers.\n<h3>In this role, you will</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Work with marketing team members to develop and implement programs for email, in-app, and other digital marketing channels for all of our product lines.</li><li>Develop and execute email nurture programs to ensure leads and customers are moving through the funnel efficiently.</li><li>Help execute existing email marketing programs by writing, building, and designing emails as necessary.</li><li>Run channel A/B tests to optimize program performance and report on results.</li><li>Help maintain database hygiene and support the team’s requests for various segmentation tasks.</li><li>Measure, analyze, and report on program performance and share actionable insights to drive ongoing improvements.</li><li>Leverage Salesforce Marketing Cloud to drive greater segmentation and email execution efficiency for the entire marketing team.</li><li>Work cross-functionally with our Marketing Operations, Brand and Creative, and Product Marketing teams.</li></ul>\n<h3>You have:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>1+ years of marketing experience, SaaS is a plus!</li><li>You have hands-on experience in a marketing automation platform: Salesforce Marketing Cloud, Hubspot, Eloqua or Pardot.</li><li>Strong fundamentals in email and in-app marketing, with an eye for optimized program performance and design.</li><li>An understanding of front-end development languages, mainly HTML &amp; CSS.</li><li>The discipline to follow a QA process to ensure successful campaign &amp; program launches.</li><li>The ability to put the customer experience at the forefront of everything by minimizing friction and creating an exceptional experience.</li><li>The drive to get the most out of technology and leverage platforms (like Salesforce) to its fullest potential.</li></ul>Why team members love working at Top Hat :<br/>*A noble mission that creates meaningful, fulfilling work*A team that cares deeply for customers and for each other*We’re a company of invested owners - every Top Hatter receives stock options*Professional learning and development for all role levels*An awesome and welcoming Toronto HQ, and a growing sales hub in Austin, Texas*Competitive health benefits that start on day one*A management team focused on performance, growth, engagement and connection*Our winning strategy and market potential*Innovative PTO policy with lots of time and space for self-care*Passionate customers that believe in us—and what we do",
